{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8889965e-19d3-47ad-a1a7-da112dc14bd1","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *above* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` is listed first.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_Uur4Cj0q5LxVvs9tmJkOIJ","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-d308be35397044df90f4542d72957ff1/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-d308be35397044df90f4542d72957ff1/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"57802207-ac53-4406-b2ae-f00f1acae6bf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), so `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`. And `Program.fs` depends on both, so it should be last.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n\n\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":462,"requestId":"1918:26F840:130CCE0:156C4C6:6A066F04"},"id":"f296f638-ab97-4b0b-b851-bd752532db18","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:55:41.730Z","parentId":"bee9da17-5853-4509-9de0-30f083547628"}
